  "title": "CANTEEN SUPERVISOR",
  "description": "<p>The Canteen Supervisor is responsible for overseeing the daily operations of the canteen, ensuring a high standard of food service, maintaining cleanliness and hygiene, managing staff, and haandling inventory.</p><p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></u></p><p><strong>Staff Management:</strong></p><ul><li>Supervise and schedule canteen staff, ensuring that the team is well-trained and motivated.</li><li>Conduct regular staff performance reviews and provide feedback.</li><li>Ensure all canteen staff adhere to health and safetyregulations and hygiene standards.</li></ul><p><strong> Food Service Operations:</strong></p><ul><li>Oversee the preparation and serving of food, ensuring timely delivery and quality service.</li><li>Ensure that food is stored, prepared, and served in compliance with food safety regulations.</li><li>Handle customer inquiries and complaints in a professional manner.</li></ul><p><strong>Inventory Management:</strong></p><ul><li>Order and manage food and beverage supplies, maintaining optimal stock levels.</li><li>Perform regular stock checks to ensure sufficient inventory and minimize waste.</li><li>Ensure the proper storage and rotation of food items according to established standards.</li></ul><p><strong>Customer Service:</strong></p><ul><li>Ensure a high standard of customer service at all times, responding to customer feedback and resolving issues promptly.</li><li>Promote a welcoming and positive atmosphere for customers.</li></ul><p><strong>Menu Planning:</strong></p><ul><li>Work with management or relevant teams to plan daily menus.</li><li>Ensure that the menu offers variety and meets the dietary requirements of all customers .</li></ul><p><u><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></u></p><p><strong>Education and Experience:</strong></p><ul><li>High school diploma or equivalent; additional certifications in hospitality, food safety, or management preferred.</li><li>Previous experience working in food service or hospitality, ideally with supervisory responsibilities.</li><li>Knowledge of food preparation, health and safety standards, and customer service.</li></ul><p><strong>Skills and Competencies:</strong></p><ul><li>Strong leadership and organizational skills to manage staff and operations effectively.</li><li>Excellent communication skills to interact with customers, staff, and management.</li><li>Ability to manage time efficiently and handle multiple tasks simultaneously.</li><li>Basic knowledge of financial management, including budgeting and inventory control.</li><li>Ability to handle stress and resolve conflicts in a calm and professional manner.</li><li>Knowledge of food safety and hygiene standards.</li></ul><p><strong>Physical Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Ability to stand for extended periods and lift heavy items (up to 30 pounds).</li><li>Comfort working in a fast-paced kitchen and canteen environment.</li></ul><p><strong>Additional Qualities: </strong></p><ul><li>Attention to detail and high standards for cleanliness and quality.</li><li>Ability to work flexible hours, including evenings or weekends, if required.</li><li>Strong problem-solving and decision-making abilities.</li></ul>",
